{"name":"Invisibility serum","type":"cypher","img":"systems/cyphersystem/icons/items/cypher.svg","system":{"version":2,"description":"<p><strong>Level:</strong> 1d6 + 2</p><p><strong>Form:</strong> Device, flask, or injection</p><p><strong>Effect:</strong> The user’s body becomes as transparent as air, making them effectively invisible for one minute per cypher level. However, their clothes and equipment are not affected, so the user must go naked if they want to be unseen. While invisible, the user is specialized in stealth and Speed defense tasks. They remain invisible even if they do something to reveal their presence or position (attacking, using an ability, moving a large object, and so on), but anyone trying to attack or physically interact with them on that turn gains an asset to do so. </p><p>Because the user is as transparent as air, when they are in water, mist, smoke, or anything other than reasonably clean air, they look like a person-shaped hole in whatever material they’re in. </p><p>The serum has detrimental effects on the mind. Each minute it is in effect, the user takes 2 points of Intellect damage. Many users have become “stuck” in the invisible state and eventually go mad as a result.</p>","archived":false,"basic":{"level":"1d6+2","identified":true},"settings":{"general":{"nameUnidentified":""}}},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"cyphersystem","systemVersion":"2.5.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1683654378132,"modifiedTime":1683655050998,"lastModifiedBy":"yThCrv1jSfPXOC2U"},"_id":"00hW0Qry5d8OFA51","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"yThCrv1jSfPXOC2U":3}}
{"name":"Ghost trap","type":"cypher","img":"systems/cyphersystem/icons/items/cypher.svg","system":{"version":2,"description":"<p><strong>Level:</strong> 1d6 + 2</p><p><strong>Form:</strong> Crystal or device</p><p><strong>Effect:</strong> Can be thrown up to a short distance, where it releases a burst of transdimensional energy in an immediate area that absorbs ghosts (including spirits, phased beings, and similar creatures) but does not affect corporeal entities. PCs who meet these criteria must use an Intellect-based action (difficulty equal to the cypher level) to avoid being trapped. NPC ghosts are not affected if their level is higher than the cypher level. The trap holds the ghosts for up to one hour per cypher level, after which they automatically break free (and are probably very angry). </p><blockquote><p>Ghosts in a trap can be permanently stored in a ghost vault.</p></blockquote>","archived":false,"basic":{"level":"1d6+2","identified":true},"settings":{"general":{"nameUnidentified":""}}},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"cyphersystem","systemVersion":"2.5.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1683651384150,"modifiedTime":1683655050997,"lastModifiedBy":"yThCrv1jSfPXOC2U"},"_id":"28ZTtZWI3TexCvnj","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"yThCrv1jSfPXOC2U":3}}
{"name":"Reanimator","type":"cypher","img":"systems/cyphersystem/icons/items/cypher.svg","system":{"version":2,"description":"<p><strong>Level:</strong> 1d6 + 2</p><p><strong>Form:</strong> Amulet or injection</p><p><strong>Effect:</strong> When used on a corpse of a creature no larger than a human, it reanimates as a violent zombie that is not under the user’s control. This reanimation process takes a few minutes (a few rounds if the cypher is level 4 or higher, or one round if level 6 or higher).</p>","archived":false,"basic":{"level":"1d6+2","identified":true},"settings":{"general":{"nameUnidentified":""}}},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"cyphersystem","systemVersion":"2.5.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1683654625296,"modifiedTime":1683655050999,"lastModifiedBy":"yThCrv1jSfPXOC2U"},"_id":"4cJZ5BwpbnA2t6Pc","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"yThCrv1jSfPXOC2U":3}}
{"name":"Anathema siren (cryptids)","type":"cypher","img":"systems/cyphersystem/icons/items/cypher.svg","system":{"version":2,"description":"<p><strong>Level:</strong> 1d6 + 2</p><p><strong>Form:</strong> Amulet or device</p><p><strong>Effect:</strong> Creates a strange and annoying noise about the volume of a human shouting. The noise is especially aggravating toward one type of creature; creatures of this type have all their actions hindered by two steps (hindered by three steps if the cypher level is 7 or higher) while within short range of the cypher. The user must use their action each round to manipulate the cypher for the noise and its effects to persist, or it goes silent and loses all power. The siren can be used for up to one minute per cypher level.</p>","archived":false,"basic":{"level":"1d6+2","identified":true},"settings":{"general":{"nameUnidentified":""}}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"yThCrv1jSfPXOC2U":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.0kHVCJ6Py5q0gL6U"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"cyphersystem","systemVersion":"2.5.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1683650532312,"modifiedTime":1683656130542,"lastModifiedBy":"yThCrv1jSfPXOC2U"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"7FHH2dQFzDuO5tRi"}
{"name":"Anathema siren","type":"cypher","img":"systems/cyphersystem/icons/items/cypher.svg","system":{"version":2,"description":"<p><strong>Level:</strong> 1d6 + 2</p><p><strong>Form:</strong> Amulet or device</p><p><strong>Effect:</strong> Creates a strange and annoying noise about the volume of a human shouting. The noise is especially aggravating toward one type of creature; creatures of this type have all their actions hindered by two steps (hindered by three steps if the cypher level is 7 or higher) while within short range of the cypher. The user must use their action each round to manipulate the cypher for the noise and its effects to persist, or it goes silent and loses all power. The siren can be used for up to one minute per cypher level. Roll a [[/r d100]] to determine what sort of creature is affected:</p><table><tbody><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">01–10</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.cyphersystem-compendium.cyphers-horror.fGiyt7f8UGuv4PBW]{Aliens} (probably one specific kind of alien)</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">11–16</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.cyphersystem-compendium.cyphers-horror.LgIEc9eEEC2n8259]{Animate dolls and puppets}</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">17–22</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.cyphersystem-compendium.cyphers-horror.7FHH2dQFzDuO5tRi]{Cryptids}</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">23–32</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.cyphersystem-compendium.cyphers-horror.epb1U7y6EZrrGYj2]{Demons}</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">33–28</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.cyphersystem-compendium.cyphers-horror.DZB8FX8d4IJMukId]{Doppelgangers}</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">39–48</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.cyphersystem-compendium.cyphers-horror.tclXQb5Wr5bXOoAw]{Ghosts}</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">49–54</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.cyphersystem-compendium.cyphers-horror.XgCPT7ToRpfuVEMm]{Mummies}</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">55–64</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.cyphersystem-compendium.cyphers-horror.JMvistOibzJM9ocJ]{Robots}</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">65–70</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.cyphersystem-compendium.cyphers-horror.cEGeMks1uc752JGB]{Simulacra}</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">71–80</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.cyphersystem-compendium.cyphers-horror.rbyrTS2eYk1x90iu]{Vampires}</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">81–90</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.cyphersystem-compendium.cyphers-horror.qqBrauJkPHI5qG0S]{Werewolves} (or some other werecreature)</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">91–95</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.cyphersystem-compendium.cyphers-horror.kwoblz3SJgPUBmXv]{Extradimensional creatures}</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">96–00</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.cyphersystem-compendium.cyphers-horror.Dy9Wwb2GIMgtreTS]{Undead}</td></tr></tbody></table>","archived":false,"basic":{"level":"1d6+2","identified":true},"settings":{"general":{"nameUnidentified":""}}},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"cyphersystem","systemVersion":"2.5.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1683650532312,"modifiedTime":1683656312082,"lastModifiedBy":"yThCrv1jSfPXOC2U"},"_id":"A1Ga365V5G9Oxl79","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"yThCrv1jSfPXOC2U":3}}
{"name":"Silgarho infusion","type":"cypher","img":"systems/cyphersystem/icons/items/cypher.svg","system":{"version":2,"description":"<p><strong>Level:</strong> 1d6</p><p><strong>Form:</strong> Flask or injection</p><p><strong>Effect:</strong> Suffuses the user’s body with a mixture of colloidal silver (sil), concentrated garlic (gar), and holy water (ho), making the user repellent to most vampires, which usually have an aversion to one or more of these materials. Vampire attacks with melee weapons against the user are hindered. Any PC vampire who attempts to feed on the user gains no sustenance and must make a Might defense roll or feel nauseous and have all their actions hindered for one minute. Any NPC vampire who attempts to feed on the user gains no sustenance and all their actions are hindered for one minute. The cypher’s effect persists in the user’s body for one day (two days if the cypher is level 4 or higher). If used directly against a vampire instead of being applied to a living creature, it affects the vampire as silver, garlic, and holy water normally would. </p><blockquote><p>Because a human body can’t dispose of colloidal silver, excessive intake of it causes a condition called argyria that turns skin purple or purple-grey.</p></blockquote>","archived":false,"basic":{"level":"1d6","identified":true},"settings":{"general":{"nameUnidentified":""}}},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"cyphersystem","systemVersion":"2.5.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1683654801239,"modifiedTime":1683655050999,"lastModifiedBy":"yThCrv1jSfPXOC2U"},"_id":"DRkZcUXoNn7GX9fb","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"yThCrv1jSfPXOC2U":3}}
